{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c24c5f09-dcb5-4ac0-afa6-1962e8c9748a",
    "name": "DYNAMOS DSP Demo (Identity -> Catalog -> Negotiation)",
    "description": "Fires the DSP-compliance chain built in T2.3/T2.4/T2.7: a real DID-verified identity, a live catalog request, and a full contract negotiation (REQUESTED -> FINALIZED) that writes a real Relation into policy-enforcer's etcd key. Assumes MVD and DYNAMOS are already deployed (configuration/dynamos-configuration.sh) and running.\n\nBefore running: run configuration/demo/mint-identity.sh once, paste the printed DAT into this collection's environment 'dat' variable.\n\nPort-forwards needed (see collection variables for exact ports):\n- kubectl -n ingress port-forward svc/nginx-nginx-ingress-controller 8080:80\n- kubectl -n negotiation-service port-forward svc/negotiation-service-vu 8092:8080\n- kubectl -n dsp-connector port-forward svc/fixture-did 8081:80\n- kubectl -n api-gateway port-forward svc/api-gateway 8095:8080 (bonus folder only)\n\nRun via Collection Runner top to bottom, or fire requests one by one in order - each request's test script hands the next request what it needs (consumerPid, providerPid), so nothing needs manual copy-pasting except the DAT once at the start.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "ingressBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8080", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "negotiationBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8092", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "fixtureDidBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8081", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "apiGatewayBaseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8095", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "dspHost", "value": "dsp-vu.dsp-connector.svc.cluster.local", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "did", "value": "did:web:fixture-did.dsp-connector.svc.cluster.local", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "party", "value": "VU", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "offerId", "value": "urn:dynamos:offer:VU:demo-identity", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "datasetId", "value": "urn:dynamos:dataset:VU:wageGap", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "consumerPid", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "providerPid", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "providerPidEnc", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0 - New Identity",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Verify new identity's DID resolves",
          "id": "2ffcda05-0af1-44b3-b23b-9561a10f9377",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{fixtureDidBaseUrl}}/.well-known/did.json", "host": ["{{fixtureDidBaseUrl}}"], "path": [".well-known", "did.json"] },
            "description": "Proves the identity minted by configuration/demo/mint-identity.sh is actually live and resolvable via did:web - this is what dsp-connector's DAT verification (dat_verification.go) resolves against on every request below. The private signing key itself was generated by that script, not inside Postman: real asymmetric key generation isn't something to do in a request tool, and even MVD's own IdentityHub doesn't hand out private keys for participants it creates (see wiki/devops/mvd-demo-dataspace-setup.md part 6)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('DID document resolves (200)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('DID matches the minted identity', function () { pm.expect(body.id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('did')); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1 - Catalog",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Request Catalog",
          "id": "c7442ed3-a7e8-4892-b72b-e84a788f44ac",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Host", "value": "{{dspHost}}" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{dat}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{ingressBaseUrl}}/api/v1/catalog/request", "host": ["{{ingressBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "catalog", "request"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "description": "Real dsp-connector-vu catalog endpoint - the Authorization bearer token is a real DAT, signature-verified against the resolved holder DID (T2.7). Returns exactly one Offer, sized to whatever Relation configuration/demo/mint-identity.sh seeded for this identity."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('consumerPid')) {",
                  "    const guid = pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}');",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('consumerPid', 'urn:example:consumer:' + guid);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Catalog request succeeds (200)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Exactly one dataset offered', function () { pm.expect(body.dataset.length).to.be.above(0); });",
                  "const ds = body.dataset[0];",
                  "const offer = ds.hasPolicy[0];",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('datasetId', ds['@id']);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('offerId', offer['@id']);",
                  "console.log('Offer to negotiate:', offer['@id'], 'for dataset', ds['@id']);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2 - Negotiation",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Initiate (REQUESTED)",
          "id": "058c43b4-dbf6-47a0-b0d8-189bdf21214e",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Host", "value": "{{dspHost}}" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{dat}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{ingressBaseUrl}}/api/v1/negotiations/request", "host": ["{{ingressBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "negotiations", "request"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"@context\": [\"https://w3id.org/dspace/2025/1/context.jsonld\"],\n  \"@type\": \"ContractRequestMessage\",\n  \"consumerPid\": \"{{consumerPid}}\",\n  \"callbackAddress\": \"https://consumer.example.com/callback\",\n  \"offer\": {\n    \"@type\": \"Offer\",\n    \"@id\": \"{{offerId}}\",\n    \"target\": \"{{datasetId}}\",\n    \"permission\": [{ \"action\": \"use\" }]\n  }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Consumer-initiated Contract Request. dsp-connector validates offer.@id against this identity's real catalog before creating anything in negotiation-service (validateOffer in negotiation_handler.go) - this is real validation, not a stub."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Negotiation created (201)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('State is REQUESTED', function () { pm.expect(body.state).to.eql('REQUESTED'); });",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('providerPid', body.providerPid);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('providerPidEnc', encodeURIComponent(body.providerPid));",
                  "console.log('providerPid:', body.providerPid);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Provider Offer (OFFERED)",
          "id": "3a304dab-544a-46fb-8e92-3da8ba42be14",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{negotiationBaseUrl}}/internal/v1/negotiations/{{providerPidEnc}}/offer", "host": ["{{negotiationBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["internal", "v1", "negotiations", "{{providerPidEnc}}", "offer"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"offer\": { \"@id\": \"{{offerId}}\", \"target\": \"{{datasetId}}\" }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Offer/Agreement are Provider-initiated per the DSP spec, delivered out-of-band to the consumer's own callback - there's deliberately no inbound dsp-connector HTTP route for them (see dsp-connector.md's endpoint reference). Reachable only via negotiation-service's own internal API directly, which is what this call does - no Authorization header, this is a cluster-internal call."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Offer accepted (200)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('State is OFFERED', function () { pm.expect(body.state).to.eql('OFFERED'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Consumer Accept (ACCEPTED)",
          "id": "e3719449-1183-45bb-8e57-fc30f7c0770c",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Host", "value": "{{dspHost}}" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{dat}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{ingressBaseUrl}}/api/v1/negotiations/{{providerPidEnc}}/events", "host": ["{{ingressBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "negotiations", "{{providerPidEnc}}", "events"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"eventType\": \"ACCEPTED\",\n  \"consumerPid\": \"{{consumerPid}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Only eventType ACCEPTED is valid on this endpoint - FINALIZED is Provider-sent and rejected here as a protocol violation (negotiation_handler.go). dsp-connector also checks this identity actually owns this providerPid before acting (the T2.3 IDOR fix)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Accepted (200)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('State is ACCEPTED', function () { pm.expect(body.state).to.eql('ACCEPTED'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Provider Agreement (AGREED)",
          "id": "97a59930-a77a-4768-a327-e74aedad48ad",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{negotiationBaseUrl}}/internal/v1/negotiations/{{providerPidEnc}}/agreement", "host": ["{{negotiationBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["internal", "v1", "negotiations", "{{providerPidEnc}}", "agreement"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"agreement\": {\n    \"@id\": \"urn:dynamos:agreement:{{party}}:postman-demo\",\n    \"target\": \"{{datasetId}}\",\n    \"assigner\": \"urn:dynamos:party:{{party}}\",\n    \"assignee\": \"mailto:{{did}}\",\n    \"permission\": [{\n      \"action\": \"dynamos:sqlDataRequest\",\n      \"constraint\": [\n        { \"leftOperand\": \"dynamos:archetype\", \"operator\": \"isAnyOf\", \"rightOperand\": [\"reproducableScience\"] },\n        { \"leftOperand\": \"dynamos:computeProvider\", \"operator\": \"isAnyOf\", \"rightOperand\": [\"otherCompany\"] }\n      ]\n    }]\n  }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Deliberately grants reproducableScience/otherCompany here - different from the demo identity's baseline Relation (computeToData/dataThroughTtp/SURF, set by mint-identity.sh) - so the bonus data-request step can prove this exact negotiation is what took effect, not the pre-existing baseline."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Agreement accepted (200)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('State is AGREED', function () { pm.expect(body.state).to.eql('AGREED'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "5. Consumer Verify (VERIFIED)",
          "id": "a32f5550-3589-4dab-8856-a0662866e7b3",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Host", "value": "{{dspHost}}" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{dat}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{ingressBaseUrl}}/api/v1/negotiations/{{providerPidEnc}}/agreement/verification", "host": ["{{ingressBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "negotiations", "{{providerPidEnc}}", "agreement", "verification"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" },
            "description": "Consumer confirms the Agreement it received. Empty body per the DSP Contract Agreement Verification Message shape."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Verified (200)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('State is VERIFIED', function () { pm.expect(body.state).to.eql('VERIFIED'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "6. Provider Finalize (FINALIZED)",
          "id": "f9d002f6-7581-4557-a855-a6a90208ad72",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{negotiationBaseUrl}}/internal/v1/negotiations/{{providerPidEnc}}/events", "host": ["{{negotiationBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["internal", "v1", "negotiations", "{{providerPidEnc}}", "events"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"eventType\": \"FINALIZED\"\n}" },
            "description": "The step that actually matters operationally: negotiation-service's FINALIZED branch (policy_enforcement.go) parses the Agreement's ODRL fields and read-modify-writes a real Relation into /policyEnforcer/agreements/{{party}}, keyed by this identity's DID. If this returns 500 policy-enforcement-failed, the negotiation deliberately stays at VERIFIED (safe retry) rather than lying about FINALIZED - check negotiation-service-vu's logs."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Finalized (200)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('State is FINALIZED', function () { pm.expect(body.state).to.eql('FINALIZED'); });",
                  "console.log('Negotiation FINALIZED - policy-enforcer\\'s etcd Relation for this identity now reflects reproducableScience/otherCompany.');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3 - Bonus: Request Data",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Request Approval (sqlDataRequest)",
          "id": "7c6e2ddd-fdd1-48fd-9bde-40156e99e68d",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{apiGatewayBaseUrl}}/api/v1/requestApproval", "host": ["{{apiGatewayBaseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "requestApproval"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"sqlDataRequest\",\n  \"user\": { \"ID\": \"postman-demo\", \"userName\": \"{{did}}\" },\n  \"dataProviders\": [\"{{party}}\"],\n  \"data_request\": {}\n}"
            },
            "description": "Drives a real sqlDataRequest through api-gateway -> orchestrator -> policy-enforcer -> vu agent, using the identity's DID as userName - exactly the Relation key the FINALIZED negotiation just wrote. Expect 202 {request_id, status: pending}. To see the actual effect: kubectl -n orchestrator logs deploy/orchestrator -c orchestrator --tail=10 | grep 'Chosen archetype' should show 'reproducableScience' (the just-negotiated archetype, not the computeToData baseline) - and policy-enforcer's restart count in `kubectl -n orchestrator get pods` must stay unchanged, proving it picked up the new Relation live with zero restart."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Request accepted (202)', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(202); });",
                  "console.log(pm.response.json());"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
